'''Muzzle blast'''
# '''Firearms Term'''. As a [[w:firearm|firearm]] (usually a [[w:rifle|rifle]], but can refer to [[w:pistol|pistol]]s as well) releases its projectile, the expanding gases from the [[muzzle]] escape at the [[crown]] through the [[bore]] in a [[flash]] of [[light]], [[heat]], and [[smoke]]. It can be so severe, as in the case of the [[w:.50 BMG|50 BMG]], as to damage the ground in front of a [[prone]] shooter. Muzzle blast is amplified by the use of [[Muzzle brake]]s.